Eli Mitnick

Bio

Eli Mitnick is a senior studying Psychology at Brown University. He is an undergraduate research assistant in Brown’s Language and Thought Lab, working on a series of experiments on deductive reasoning and pragmatics with the lab’s PI, Roman Feiman.

Education

Brown University | Providence, RI

Psychology Sc.B. | September 2017 - May 2021

Experience

Brown University, Language and Thought Lab | Undergraduate Research Assistant | September 2020 - Present
